Jelly tints have been going viral—and here’s my take! 💖
You’ve seen the Indian Brand @praush.beauty Jelly Tint in most of my GRWM reels—super easy to use, long-lasting, and gives a soft, non-dark stain that lasts beautifully through the day.
Recently tried the @sheglam_official Jelly Tint—high pigment, super strong tint, so go light-handed and blend fast! ✨ you can get yours from @the_makeup_house 
Pro tip: Always use a brush or blend immediately for a flawless finish.

If you’ve got warm undertones or medium to tan skin, the Laura Mercier Honey Setting Powder is made for you. 🍯
This cult-favorite finely milled formula sets makeup like a dream, blurs pores, and controls shine—all without flashback.
It’s lightweight, long-lasting, and gives that soft-matte filtered finish we all love.
A little goes a long way—so yes, it’s absolutely value for money.
